{
  "texts": [
    "The size (length) of the provided text has no limit (depends on the users' needs and interests) for our system, due to the keywords extraction feature in the first stages, which disregards all unnecessary words (i.e., stop-words or words that have no value for the scientific area of computer science).",
    "Details are found in Sect. 3.3.",
    "Also, users with userID in the range [3,6] (Table 9) provide a list of papers they have already liked, so that the system can use this information in the CF method.The artificial users, at the same time, provide the ground truth data utilized in calculating specific metrics (described in paragraph 2.4) for the evaluation of the system.",
    "In case the user provides some text of interest (e.g., abstract/ keywords/ full paper, etc.",
    "), the system retrieves from AMiner citation-network dataset the papers that are found to have the highest cosine similarity with the text of interest; this set of papers along with their referenced papers create a bigger set of papers that are the ground truth data for the artificial users."
  ]
}